<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Enterprise Technology and Delivery provides continuous operating, computing and telecommunications services to business partners within the bank. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Technology couples technological expertise with the firm&#39;s strategic vision to keep the firm at the forefront of the world&#39;s financial markets. Delivering market-leading technology drives our business forward.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Infrastructure covers the firm&#39;s core networks, data centers, and end-user services, which underpin our corporate and business platforms and connect our employees, clients, suppliers, and vendors together. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
You will join a 2 year rotation programme and will have two year long placements within the division. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
Responsibilities can range from establishing a distributed computing framework using in-house developed technologies to being the system administrator for a global UNIX platform, or be providing first-level support on one of our state-of-the-art trading systems.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
We carefully match the skills and experiences shown through the interview process to ensure that all new starters have a rich and varied working experience, gaining the expertise critical to build a technology career within the banking industry. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
As an analyst within Technology you will: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future career options and opportunities </li>	
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally </li>	
	<li>Collaborate on exciting global projects that contribute to business success and next-generation advances </li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking and written and oral communications skills.  In addition you must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain a minimum 2:1 degree or equivalent.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
Underlying all this, you must demonstrate dedication to a career in banking technology. It is our commitment to you, to develop you as specialist banking technologists, not technologists who happen to be working in the banking industry.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Depending on which group successful candidates join training will begin in the US initially with analysts from all lines of business.  The programme is a combination of classroom instruction, e-learning modules, case studies and presentations. Throughout the tuition period, analysts have ample opportunities to work closely with professionals and peers across Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America. This is a great opportunity to build a network of colleagues from across the company which will prove to be a tremendous resource throughout your career with the bank. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America places a great deal of emphasis on on-going training for all staff.  Training modules are available to all levels from product specific courses to generic soft skills development.  Whether a new graduate, or seasoned professional, expanding the skills of the associates is paramount to achieving success.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The analyst position is challenging, fast-paced, and requires a great deal of enthusiasm for both technology and the financial services industry. Analysts will be placed in one of our three London sites, Camberley or Croydon; Offers are made for a specific office or group, based on candidate preference and business need. 
</p>

